cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of novelty detection in multimedia data using a deep learning framework. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of mixup technique and novel loss function for training the network indicates that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The evaluation on benchmark datasets related to image classification such as Caltech-256 and Stanford Dogs further supports the likelihood of cs.CV and cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-categories. Finally, the use of deep learning and training without auxiliary datasets suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
